🧠 2) DSA — BINARY SEARCH (VERY IMPORTANT)
🔥 Core Idea

Binary search is used when:

data is sorted
you want fast lookup
🔹 Basic Implementation
def binary_search(arr, target):
    left, right = 0, len(arr) - 1

    while left <= right:
        mid = (left + right) // 2

        if arr[mid] == target:
            return mid
        elif arr[mid] < target:
            left = mid + 1
        else:
            right = mid - 1

    return -1
🧠 Deep Understanding
✔ Why fast?

👉 Each step cuts search space in half

Time: O(log n)
Space: O(1)
🔥 Real-Time Usage
✔ Trading Systems
find price in sorted order book
search trade history
✔ Databases
indexing (B-trees use binary search internally)
✔ API systems
search user records
locate transactions
🧠 GS-Level Answer

👉 Question: “When do you use binary search?”

💬 Strong Answer:

“Binary search is used when data is sorted or can be sorted efficiently. It reduces time complexity from O(n) to O(log n), making it ideal for high-performance systems such as searching in large datasets, order books, or indexed database queries.”

🔥 Advanced Variations (IMPORTANT)
✔ First Occurrence
# lower bound
✔ Last Occurrence
# upper bound
✔ Search in rotated array

👉 Common GS question

✔ Binary search on answer

👉 Example:

