🧠 2) DSA — BINARY SEARCH (DEEP + REAL SYSTEMS)
🔥 Core Idea

Binary search = divide search space exponentially

🧠 Deep Insight

👉 Instead of checking every element:

N → N/2 → N/4 → N/8 → ...

👉 That’s why:

Time = O(log n)
Extremely scalable
🔥 Real-Time Usage (VERY IMPORTANT)
✔ 1. Trading Systems
Order book sorted by price
find best bid/ask quickly
✔ 2. Databases
indexes (B-Trees)
searching millions of rows
✔ 3. Rate Limiting / Capacity

👉 Example:

find minimum servers needed
max throughput
🧠 GS-Level Answer

Q: When do you use binary search?

“Binary search is used when the data is sorted or when we can define a monotonic search space. It reduces search time from O(n) to O(log n), making it highly efficient for large-scale systems like databases, trading engines, and search services.”

🔥 Advanced Patterns (VERY IMPORTANT)
✔ 1. Lower Bound

👉 first position ≥ target

✔ 2. Upper Bound

👉 first position > target

✔ 3. Binary Search on Answer (TOP GS QUESTION)
Example:

👉 “Minimum capacity to ship packages in D days”

👉 You don’t search array
👉 You search answer space

💬 GS-Level Answer

“Even if data is not sorted, we can use binary search on the answer space when the problem has a monotonic property, allowing us to efficiently converge to the optimal solution.”

✔ 4. Rotated Sorted Array

👉 common GS problem

⚠️ Common Mistakes

❌ infinite loop (left < right vs <=)
❌ wrong mid calculation
❌ ignoring edge cases

